# npm / node commands in this project

When running **npm** or **node** (e.g. `npm install`, `npm run dev`, `npx`) in the terminal, prepend PATH so Homebrew's Node is used and Volta is bypassed. Otherwise the sandbox may hit "Volta error: Node is not available".

Use:

```bash
PATH="/opt/homebrew/bin:/usr/local/bin:$PATH" npm install
```

or for any npm/node command:

```bash
PATH="/opt/homebrew/bin:/usr/local/bin:$PATH" <command>
```

Examples:
- `PATH="/opt/homebrew/bin:/usr/local/bin:$PATH" npm install`
- `PATH="/opt/homebrew/bin:/usr/local/bin:$PATH" npm run dev`
- `PATH="/opt/homebrew/bin:/usr/local/bin:$PATH" npx shadcn@latest add button`
